{"parse":{"title":"Andrew Hussey","pageid":8233711,"revid":846616477,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">Not to be confused with <a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Hussey_Allen\" title=\"Andrew Hussey Allen\">Andrew Hussey Allen</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Andrew_Hussie\" title=\"Andrew Hussie\">Andrew Hussie</a>.</div>\n<p><b>Andrew Hussey</b> <a href=\"/wiki/Order_of_the_British_Empire\" title=\"Order of the British Empire\">OBE</a> (born 1963) is an <a href=\"/wiki/English_people\" title=\"English people\">English</a> historian of <a href=\"/wiki/Culture_of_France\" title=\"Culture of France\">French</a> culture and biographer. He has published multiple books, focusing primarily on 20th century French history and <a href=\"/wiki/Biography\" title=\"Biography\">biography</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Media_appearances\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Media appearances</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Honours\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Honours</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Publications</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#TV_works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">TV works</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Radio\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Radio</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life\">Early life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Born in <a href=\"/wiki/Liverpool\" title=\"Liverpool\">Liverpool</a>, Hussey was educated at the <a href=\"/wiki/Victoria_University_of_Manchester\" title=\"Victoria University of Manchester\">University of Manchester</a> and the <a href=\"/wiki/Jean_Moulin_University_Lyon_3\" title=\"Jean Moulin University Lyon 3\">Jean Moulin University Lyon 3</a>. He received his PhD for a thesis on <a href=\"/wiki/Georges_Bataille\" title=\"Georges Bataille\">Georges Bataille</a>, eventually published as his first book.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>His biography of <a href=\"/wiki/Guy_Debord\" title=\"Guy Debord\">Guy Debord</a> was named by <a href=\"/wiki/Julian_Barnes\" title=\"Julian Barnes\">Julian Barnes</a> as International Book of the Year in the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Times_Literary_Supplement\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Times Literary Supplement\">Times Literary Supplement</a></i> in 2001.\n</p>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><div class=\"center\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Audio-input-microphone.svg/50px-Audio-input-microphone.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Audio-input-microphone.svg/75px-Audio-input-microphone.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c0/Audio-input-microphone.svg/100px-Audio-input-microphone.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"48\" data-file-height=\"48\" /></div></div></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\" style=\"line-height:1.1em\"><div class=\"haudio\">\n<div style=\"padding:4px 0\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac\" title=\"File:Andrew Hussey BBC Radio4 Start the Week 24 Nov 2008 b00fkw8j.flac\"><center>Andrew Hussey's voice</center></a></div>\n<div><div class=\"mediaContainer\" style=\"width:220px\"><audio id=\"mwe_player_0\" controls=\"\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width:220px\" class=\"kskin\" data-durationhint=\"36.961333333333\" data-startoffset=\"0\" data-mwtitle=\"Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac\" data-mwprovider=\"wikimediacommons\"><source src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/5/59/Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac/Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac.ogg\" type=\"audio/ogg; codecs=&quot;vorbis&quot;\" data-title=\"Ogg Vorbis\" data-shorttitle=\"Ogg Vorbis\" data-transcodekey=\"ogg\" data-width=\"0\" data-height=\"0\" data-bandwidth=\"104520\" /><source src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/transcoded/5/59/Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac/Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac.mp3\" type=\"audio/mpeg\" data-title=\"MP3\" data-shorttitle=\"MP3\" data-transcodekey=\"mp3\" data-width=\"0\" data-height=\"0\" data-bandwidth=\"246800\" /><source src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/59/Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac\" type=\"audio/flac\" data-title=\"Original FLAC file (731 kbps)\" data-shorttitle=\"FLAC source\" data-width=\"0\" data-height=\"0\" data-bandwidth=\"730827\" /></audio></div></div>\n<div class=\"description\" style=\"padding:2px 0 0 0\"><center><a href=\"/wiki/File:Andrew_Hussey_BBC_Radio4_Start_the_Week_24_Nov_2008_b00fkw8j.flac\" title=\"File:Andrew Hussey BBC Radio4 Start the Week 24 Nov 2008 b00fkw8j.flac\">Recorded November 2008</a> from the BBC Radio 4 programme <i><a href=\"/wiki/Start_the_Week\" title=\"Start the Week\">Start the Week</a></i></center></div></div></td></tr>\n<tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"mbox-text\" style=\"line-height:1.1em\"><hr /><span><i>Problems playing this file? See <a href=\"/wiki/Help:Media\" title=\"Help:Media\">media help</a>.</i></span></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>Hussey lectured in French at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Huddersfield\" title=\"University of Huddersfield\">University of Huddersfield</a> in the 1990s.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He was a senior lecturer in French at the <a href=\"/wiki/Aberystwyth_University\" title=\"Aberystwyth University\">University of Wales Aberystwyth</a> and since 2006 he has been the dean of the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_London_Institute_in_Paris\" title=\"University of London Institute in Paris\">University of London Institute in Paris</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In 2014 he was appointed Director of the Centre for Post-Colonial Studies at the University of London's <a href=\"/wiki/School_of_Advanced_Study\" title=\"School of Advanced Study\">School of Advanced Study</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He began his career as a journalist writing for <a href=\"/wiki/Julie_Burchill\" title=\"Julie Burchill\">Julie Burchill</a>'s <i><a href=\"/wiki/Modern_Review_(London)\" title=\"Modern Review (London)\">Modern Review</a></i> in the early 1990s. He now regularly contributes to <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Observer\" title=\"The Observer\">The Observer</a></i>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_Statesman\" title=\"New Statesman\">New Statesman</a></i>, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Granta\" title=\"Granta\">Granta</a></i> and <i><a href=\"/wiki/Literary_Review\" title=\"Literary Review\">Literary Review</a></i>.\n</p><p>In 2007, Hussey provided the foreword to <i>How to Enjoy Paris in 1842</i>, written by <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_Herv%C3%A9\" title=\"Francis Herv\u00e9\">Francis Herv\u00e9</a>. He is best known for his book <i>Paris: The Secret History,</i><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact\" style=\"white-space:nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed\" title=\"Wikipedia:Citation needed\"><span title=\"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (June 2018)\">citation needed</span></a></i>&#93;</sup> described by <a href=\"/wiki/Peter_Ackroyd\" title=\"Peter Ackroyd\">Peter Ackroyd</a> in <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Times\" title=\"The Times\">The Times</a></i> as \"endlessly informative, with a story on every page\". It was well reviewed in the United Kingdom, the United States and in France, where it was shortlisted for the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Prix_Grandgousier&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Prix Grandgousier (page does not exist)\">Prix Grandgousier</a>, and has been translated into ten languages.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Media_appearances\">Media appearances</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Media appearances\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Hussey also presents television documentaries, amongst which is <i>France on a Plate</i>, first broadcast in December 2009. In this programme, he discusses the culinary history of France in relation to its political and social history.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Honours\">Honours</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Honours\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>He was appointed <a href=\"/wiki/Officer_of_the_Order_of_the_British_Empire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Officer of the Order of the British Empire\">Officer of the Order of the British Empire</a> (OBE) in the 2011 New Year Honours for services to UK/France cultural relations.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Publications\">Publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>The Inner Scar: The Mysticism of <a href=\"/wiki/Georges_Bataille\" title=\"Georges Bataille\">Georges Bataille</a></i> (2000)</li>\n<li><i>The Game of War: The Life and Death of <a href=\"/wiki/Guy_Debord\" title=\"Guy Debord\">Guy Debord</a></i> (2001)</li>\n<li><i>The Beast at Heaven\u2019s Gate: Georges Bataille and the Art of Transgression</i> (2006)</li>\n<li><i>Paris: The Secret History</i> (2006)</li>\n<li><i>The French Intifada&#160;: The Long War Between France and its Arabs</i> (2014)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"TV_works\">TV works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: TV works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i>France on a Plate</i> <a href=\"/wiki/BBC_Four\" title=\"BBC Four\">BBC Four</a> (2010)</li>\n<li><i>The North on a Plate</i> BBC Four (2011)</li>\n<li><i>Treasures of the Louvre</i> BBC Four (2013)</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Radio\">Radio</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Radio\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Albert_Camus\" title=\"Albert Camus\">Albert Camus</a> - Inside the Outsider</i> BBC Radio 3 (2013)<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Hussey&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/45px-Commons-logo.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/59px-Commons-logo.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1024\" data-file-height=\"1376\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Wikimedia Commons has media related to <i><b><a href=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Andrew_Hussey\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"commons:Category:Andrew Hussey\">Andrew Hussey</a></b></i>.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">7 April 1997 (1997-04-04). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/story.asp?storyCode=160314&amp;sectioncode=20\">\"Conflict and the poetics of a fragile space &#124; Art &amp; design\"</a>. Times Higher Education<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2014-08-09</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Conflict+and+the+poetics+of+a+fragile+space+%26%23124%3B+Art+%26+design&amp;rft.pub=Times+Higher+Education&amp;rft.date=1997-04-04&amp;rft.au=7+April+1997&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.timeshighereducation.co.uk%2Fstory.asp%3FstoryCode%3D160314%26sectioncode%3D20&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAndrew+Hussey\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.ulip.lon.ac.uk/staff/staff/staff-profiles/andrew-hussey.html\">[1]</a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20090225075230/http://www.ulip.lon.ac.uk/staff/staff/staff-profiles/andrew-hussey.html\">Archived</a> February 25, 2009, at the <a href=\"/wiki/Wayback_Machine\" title=\"Wayback Machine\">Wayback Machine</a>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite